race.comment: NOLAN (1) resumes here but the form he displayed when last in work was good enough for a race of this calibre. Is yet to miss a drum in four spins around this circuit and gets some well-needed weight relief with the 3kg claim. Looks very hard to toss while fresh. CHARTWELL (2) is another first-up but has placed two from three over this track and trip and is usually thereabouts. Include in calculations. KHUMBILA (10) placed over this course and distance when having the first run for the new stable and will have come on with that run under the belt. In the mix. The well-related TRAPASSI (18) (half to G1 winner Beiwacht) best of the rest.
